### 5. Why 7+ Quantum Gravity Programs All Converge on d_s → 2

**Source:** Atlas — QG1, Strategy 001-002

**The result:** The convergence of spectral dimension d_s → 2 across CDT, asymptotic safety, string theory, LQG, Horava-Lifshitz, causal sets, and noncommutative geometry is not coincidental. All these approaches are approximating the same UV physics: quadratic gravity with fakeons. Each captures part of the picture — CDT sees d_s ≈ 2 numerically, asymptotic safety sees anomalous dimension η = 2, strings see 2D thermodynamics, etc.

**Why it matters:** Unifies the landscape conceptually. Explains why independent approaches converge on a single mathematical structure rather than being a coincidence.

